Database migrations (Flask-Migrate / Alembic).

Common commands (run inside the api container or a local venv):

    flask --app app.main db upgrade            # apply migrations
    flask --app app.main db migrate -m "msg"   # autogenerate a new revision
    flask --app app.main db downgrade -1       # roll back one

The initial revision (0001_initial) creates every table in app/models.
